  "5.16": "600381 8000800) Different, what we do is different. For this reason\nSome say one thing on the outside and do the opposite on the inside.\nEven Duryodhana said \"I know what I am doing is wrong\".\nHere we have to note what has been said. He knew what religion was. He is though\nHeld according to his nature. So our understanding is different, our action is different. Our nature is all of us\nPut aside study, intellect, rationalism and make us do the work according to nature\nleaves This is what Krishna is saying here as \"the pioneer of nature\". What is your nature-\nSuch is your tendency. God will raise you accordingly. which of whom\nIf there is a nature, they should be the same and not like the other. If the mango fruit turns sour\nIt is a bad fruit, the more sour the tamarind fruit the better. Hence the tamas\nBeing like tamas is their natural dharma. As is one's natural nature, so is natural\nThe act of cultivation in nature was done by the Lord who is free. The fruit of everything\nHe is the Giver. He has never been arrested.\n\nThus this verse is the answer to all our doubts. Our doubts are profound. to the mind\nDoubt that comes can be removed but doubt that comes to mind (17891901031 60000\nDifficult to overcome. According to the ancient writers of psychology this is called 'stirasasamshaya'\ncalled 'I am smarter than everyone else' in the material world of ours\nMakes you know. Because of this we do not acclimate our mind towards the truth\nIt does not give us faith. Whatever we do, we know it and believe it\n\nshould do For that classical feeling is important at every step.  I mean, nature\nThat is, what is that power that governs my nature, that holds the hand and is the fruit\nWhen you know who the giver is, etc., there is no room for ego.\n\nHere we have a question. Why does God punish us? God punishes us\nGiving is not out of hatred, but behind it is immense-infinite compassion. Mother punishes the child\nKindness behind giving is somehow like that. Life is from the sorrows that come in life\nwill be cooked. We should be prepared for the heat of the heat that comes to us in life, Bendu\nMust mature. He who does not see difficulties in life never grows. Another's happiness for him-\nSadness is not understood. When life is difficult, it is difficult. This is what the Lord gives us\nMercy behind punishment. Behind our fall lies a seed of redemption. Behind the sadness\nThere is a seed of happiness. Thus when viewed classically, the universal power behind the entire world, Maha\nProtecting us as Karunyamurthy. The warning comes. A child who does not have the strength to wake up\nJust as a mother takes care of us, so the Lord is always protecting us. This is\nIntuition must be constant on the spiritual path.",
