  "9.21": "Te tam bhuktva swarga lokam vishalam ksheene punye martya lokam vishanti.\nevam three dharmam anuprapannah gata agatam kama kama: labhante - He is wide\n\nAfter finding the land of Saggigara, they return to earth when the merit is over. Thus the cry of Vedic karmas\nHokku wanders here and there on the back of desires.\n\nThe Triavidians who perform pious deeds with the desire of heaven join heaven and enjoy all kinds of pleasures there\nAs soon as they experience the fruit of their good deeds, they are born again in the earth. Because of this\nHe is from the greatest salvation and from the Lord. will be deprived. He always\nThey get stuck in the cycle of desires. A very different move from them is that of the participants:\n\nAnanyashchintayanto maam ye janah paryupasate |\nTesham nityabhiuktanam yogksheman vahamyaham",
