  "16.18": "Ahankaram balam darpam kaman krodham cha samsritah.\nMam atma paradeheshu pradvishantah abhyasuyakah -- the abode of anger, compulsion, arrogance, desire, anger. Those who do not believe in me within their own and others' bodies and deny it. Those who are excited about the prosperity of others.\n\nHis basic properties are - Ahamkara, Darpa, Kama and Rodha. Who can surpass me? The pride that I am a big man. It is supported by money and power. This is a form of looking down on others. The desires of the coast, the anger that they are not fulfilled - this is their existence. Krishna says: \"Don't believe in the 'I' within everyone\nThis is not denying God temporarily for some reason, but denying God by nature. Such people are always jealous of the knowledge and wealth of others.",
