  "16.10": "Kamam Ashritya Dushburam Dambha Mana Mada Anvitah.\n\nMohat grihitva asat grahan pravarthante ashuchi vratah - the backbone of inexhaustible desire\nHypocrisy, pride and arrogance. These people are guilty of dirty deeds\nThey live based on perceptions.\n\nThere is no end to the desires of the demoniac. No matter how much it comes, there is still more. For example work itself\nIf not, he wants a job, when he gets a job, he wants more salary, when he gets a salary, that salary is his\nLess than the next-door neighbor-so much for wanting a higher salary, a bigger position, and so on\nEven if you get it, you are not satisfied. This thirst cannot be satisfied. As the legend says, how\nJust as the underworld cannot be covered with dirt, so as to fulfill man's desire\ncan't No matter how much money we get, we are one zero to the right of it\nWe lament that it was reduced by inclusion. And forget happiness.\nIn Kathopanishad - when Yama says \"I will give you as much money as you want\",\nNachiketa says: “Na wittena tarpaniyo manshinah”. It means “man's wealth\n\nNo one can fulfill the desire.” Sufficient is the divine nature, need\nIt is demonic nature. Thus the demonic nature is the back of desires, the desire of that shore\nThey do what they shouldn't do to get revenge. His life is hypocrisy. bigumana,\nArrogance, deceiving others with a dramatic life. Walk like this\nA dirty life without cleanliness is theirs.\n\nChintamaparimeyam cha pralayanthampasritah |\nKamopabhogaparama etavavaditi seshikah",
