  "16.15": "Idam adya maya labdham imam propsye manoratham.\n\nIdam asti idam api mei bhaivati ​​punradhanam ॥\n\nAsau maya hatah shatruh hanishye cha apa ran api.\n\nIshvarah aham aham bhogi siddha aham balwan sukhee ॥\n\nAdhyo abhijanavan asmi kah anyah asti sadrishah maya |\n\nyakshye dasyami modishye iti ajnana vimohitah - he ignorantly said that\nPoor man: I got this now; I will fulfill this wish further; This too\nThere is; Again this will be mine; Killed this hatred; Gonna finish the rest too; i am\nAlmighty; I am the indulger; I am the one who got everything I wanted; Powerful and happy;\nI am sick; I am noble; Who is compared to me? I will perform yaga. charity\nI will give I am glad.\n\nIn these three slokas, Krishna tells us what the thoughts of the demons are like\nexplained. The idea is that they should always collect money. When he got it, he said, “That's it for today\nGot it, I will earn this much tomorrow'. Collecting money is an addiction for them. to himself\nThe thought that I have finished the one who did not become, will finish the one who will not become. I am omnipotent,\nWhat is in this world because of me? I was born to be happy—not to be sad; For my happiness\nI will do anything; I will finish those who cross it; I am a ready man;\n\nI am responsible for my success; I was born to be happy, people-money-power\nI have; As I wish. I walk; Money can buy something; to me\nmatch Who is in this world? - etc. his thoughts. A sacrifice for appearances\nDoing yagadis and giving charity is their constant activity. This is the dance of ignorance.\nThey do not know that this is the gateway to their destruction. The same magnificence, the same auspiciousness\n\nThey live in the illusion that\n\nVaengchittavibhranta mohajalasamavritah |\nPrasaktah Kamabhogeshu Patanti Narake*shuchau",
